<statement><div><p>The figure below shows a pyramid with a triangular base. The base of the triangle measures <m>{18}\,\text{m}</m>, the height of the triangle is <m>{3}\,\text{m}</m>, and the vertical height of the pyramid is <m>{28}\,\text{m}</m>. Find the volume of the pyramid.</p>
<p><m>\text{Volume}=</m><fillin characters="7" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{m}^3</m></p></div></statement>
<solution><div><p><alert>Given:</alert></p>
<p>
Base of triangle, <m>b = {18}\,\text{m}</m><br/>
Height of triangle, <m>h = {3}\,\text{m}</m><br/>
Vertical height of pyramid, <m>H = {28}\,\text{m}</m>
</p>

<ol type="i">
  <li>
    <p>Compute the area of the triangular base:</p>
    <p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Base area} \amp = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height of triangle}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{1}{2} \times {18} \times {3}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {27}\,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Compute the volume of the pyramid using <m>V = \frac{1}{3} \times \text{Base area} \times \text{vertical height}</m>:</p>
    <p>
<md>
<mrow>V \amp = \frac{1}{3} \times {27} \times {28}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {252}\,\text{m}^3</mrow>
</md>
    </p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p>
Therefore,<br/>
The volume of the pyramid is <m> {252}\,\text{m}^3</m> </p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>252</m></p></answer>
